The code synthesizes the results from previous steps to construct a comprehensive classification matrix that maps each physical mechanism to its corresponding effective theory. It loads the Hurst exponent $H$, the tail index $\alpha$, Kullback-Leibler (KL) divergence, the ballistic peak ratio for the Lévy-Lorentz gas, and the Tsallis $q$-index for the Sisyphus cooling models. Each mechanism is assigned an effective theory operator based on its physical nature. The classification matrix is printed to the console and saved as a CSV file. 

